1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,545
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,628 --> 00:00:05,964
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:10,677
♪ <i>Fix this, oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:14,431
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled…</i> ♪

6
00:00:14,514 --> 00:00:15,640
[Audrey, in English] <i>Is this Mr. Mercado?</i>

7
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:18,768
I want to meet the Master Cutter.

8
00:00:18,852 --> 00:00:20,145
[phone rings]

9
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:22,439
Let's avoid those things.

10
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:25,191
I'm done with family drama.

11
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:26,651
Brother Atoy, you're a fan of Raki too?

12
00:00:26,735 --> 00:00:27,861
[Atoy] Do you know him?

13
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:30,530
[Atoy] <i>He's the primary suspect</i>
<i>in Queenie's disappearance.</i>

14
00:00:30,613 --> 00:00:31,656
[Karla] <i>He's a kidnapper?!</i>

15
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:34,909
He has a punk rock band, Munting Sigaw.

16
00:00:34,993 --> 00:00:35,827
[gasps]

17
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:36,619
Oh, why?

18
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,330
[Ibyang] <i>That's what Sis Tonet</i>
<i>was listening to earlier.</i>

19
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:40,206
[Atoy] <i>Where's Tonet?</i>

20
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:42,167
[Cita] <i>She said she'd go straight</i>
<i>to her appointment.</i>

21
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:43,334
Let's go!

22
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:45,837
Just because you're a rockstar
doesn't mean you can get everything!

23
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,005
[Enzo] <i>Leave Tonet alone!</i>

24
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:48,965
[Atoy, Emerson, in English] Rock on!

25
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:52,302
[Atoy] <i>Raki's band, Munting Sigaw…</i>

26
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:53,887
Do you know if they're here?

27
00:00:53,970 --> 00:00:55,847
[Enzo] <i>Yes, sir.</i>
<i>They're in the green room.</i>

28
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:58,058
[Tonet] <i>I feel dizzy.</i>

29
00:00:58,141 --> 00:00:59,434
You know, it's too noisy here.

30
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:01,394
Better if we step outside,
so you can get some air.

31
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:03,271
Hey, wait. No entry unless you're staff.

32
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:05,940
How are you? Let's talk outside.

33
00:01:06,941 --> 00:01:10,153
Okay, let's talk outside.
I've got nothing to hide.

34
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:11,905
Come on.

35
00:01:11,988 --> 00:01:14,741
[music continues]

36
00:01:18,536 --> 00:01:20,080
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

37
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:24,626
[rock music playing]

38
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:28,087
[Enzo] Slowly.

39
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:29,631
[music continues]

40
00:01:29,714 --> 00:01:31,257
- [Tonet groans]
- [Enzo groans]

41
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:34,969
[music continues]

42
00:01:41,976 --> 00:01:43,228
[car door clicks shut]

43
00:01:43,311 --> 00:01:46,272
[music continues]

44
00:01:52,153 --> 00:01:53,363
[car door clicks shut]

45
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:56,282
[ominous music playing]

46
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:58,868
What's your address?

47
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:06,751
Just take me to Delfin's Tailoring,

48
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:08,962
Barangay Tabang Lupa.

49
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:11,339
[in English] Thank you, Enzo.

50
00:02:11,923 --> 00:02:13,299
I'll just look for the map.

51
00:02:14,008 --> 00:02:15,218
Just relax.

52
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:19,013
[sinister music playing]

53
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:26,646
[car engine starts]

54
00:02:26,729 --> 00:02:29,899
[foreboding music playing]

55
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:36,823
- [crowd cheering]
- [hard rock song playing]

56
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,248
[in English] Rock and roll!

57
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:48,293
[crowd cheering]

58
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:49,961
[in English] Rock and roll!

59
00:02:50,044 --> 00:02:51,671
[crowd cheering]

60
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:55,258
[in English] Hey, hey, hey!

61
00:02:56,092 --> 00:02:59,762
We've got a jaywalker from Munting Sigaw!

62
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:03,349
[in English] Raki Roman in the house!

63
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:06,519
[crowd cheering]

64
00:03:06,603 --> 00:03:08,229
[hard rock music playing]

65
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:11,816
[in English] Rock!

66
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,276
♪ <i>Wait! Who is this?</i> ♪

67
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:15,737
♪ <i>Knows too much, knows too much</i> ♪

68
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:16,905
♪ <i>Knows too much</i> ♪

69
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:17,947
♪ <i>Wait! Who is this?</i> ♪

70
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,241
♪ <i>Knows too much, knows too much</i> ♪

71
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:21,951
♪ <i>Knows too much</i> ♪

72
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:23,244
♪ <i>Wait! Who is this?</i> ♪

73
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:26,164
♪ <i>Knows too much about the people</i>
<i>Who walk out of the motels</i> ♪

74
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:31,502
[continues singing]

75
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:33,087
[in English] Rock and roll!

76
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:35,548
- [crowd cheering]
- [music continues]

77
00:03:41,971 --> 00:03:44,015
Oh! Where are you going?

78
00:03:44,098 --> 00:03:45,808
[crowd cheering]

79
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:48,353
[in English] Rock and roll!

80
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:49,938
[crowd cheering]

81
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,856
[hard rock music playing]

82
00:03:52,607 --> 00:03:53,650
[Raki] Huh?

83
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,735
[crowd cheering]

84
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:57,946
You even took a nosedive
just to escape, huh?

85
00:03:58,029 --> 00:03:59,280
Come on. Come with me!

86
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,159
[crowd cheering]

87
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:07,789
[hard rock music playing]

88
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:09,832
[growls]

89
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,585
[suave theme music playing]

90
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:16,881
[sewing machine whirring]

91
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:18,466
[scratches]

92
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:25,181
[gunshots blasting]

93
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:29,560
[music intensifies]

94
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,152
I'm telling the truth.

95
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:40,905
I had nothing to do with Mandy's
or Queenie's disappearance!

96
00:04:41,572 --> 00:04:43,408
I'm a player, not a kidnapper!

97
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:47,036
As for why they disappeared,
I have no idea!

98
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:49,038
[in English] "Player, player".

99
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:50,957
Where did you take them?

100
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,583
Just here at On the Edge.

101
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,335
I get discounts on food and drinks there.

102
00:04:54,419 --> 00:04:57,213
Besides, I only allot three hours
maximum for a date with me.

103
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:59,090
I'm a busy man too.

104
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:01,843
Then why did you run from us?

105
00:05:01,926 --> 00:05:03,219
You look guilty.

106
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:06,014
Well, maybe you're assets or cops.

107
00:05:06,097 --> 00:05:07,098
Of course I don't want to be
dragged to the police station.

108
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:08,099
That's risky.

109
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:10,101
Where's Tonet? Where is she?

110
00:05:10,184 --> 00:05:12,020
Is she your date tonight?

111
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:13,479
‪[Atoy] Oh.

112
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:15,565
You were together.

113
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:18,526
There's a picture of you two
on your band's website.

114
00:05:18,609 --> 00:05:20,278
Here, you're talking to her.

115
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:24,449
Hmm, but I already searched the whole bar.

116
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:27,410
I checked everywhere, even the bathrooms.

117
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,037
I didn't see her. Where did you take her?!

118
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:32,874
I just saw her, but she was not my date!

119
00:05:32,957 --> 00:05:34,292
I…

120
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:37,503
I couldn't even make a move.
Enzo was guarding her.

121
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:39,964
So, they're the ones who are close.

122
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:41,758
Ask Enzo.

123
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:43,676
Enzo?

124
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,386
[suspicious music playing]

125
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,637
Who's Enzo?

126
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:48,639
Where can we find him?

127
00:05:48,723 --> 00:05:52,143
[foreboding music playing]

128
00:06:07,116 --> 00:06:08,201
Tonet.

129
00:06:08,284 --> 00:06:10,661
[music continues]

130
00:06:12,371 --> 00:06:13,456
Tonet.

131
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:20,671
Looks like the effect of my…

132
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:23,174
special drink is potent.

133
00:06:23,674 --> 00:06:25,802
[music swells]

134
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,310
[in English] Welcome home.

135
00:06:34,393 --> 00:06:36,145
[music continues]

136
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:38,147
Later, I'll introduce you…

137
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:43,027
to one of my friends. Once you wake up.

138
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:45,655
[music fades]

139
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:52,370
[ominous music playing]

140
00:07:00,461 --> 00:07:05,383
[music intensifies]

141
00:07:50,219 --> 00:07:52,305
[rock music playing]

142
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:53,848
Wait! I'll show you!

143
00:07:53,931 --> 00:07:54,849
How will you know?!

144
00:07:57,185 --> 00:07:59,896
There! That's Enzo.

145
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:01,564
He was here earlier.

146
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,941
She's dating him, not me.

147
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:07,028
[ominous music playing]

148
00:08:08,237 --> 00:08:10,364
I asked him earlier.

149
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,035
But he wasn't with Tonet.

150
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:18,289
- You're a liar!
- Enzo is the liar!

151
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:20,833
[rock music playing]

152
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:25,463
He's a Gemini, not an Aries.

153
00:08:25,546 --> 00:08:28,549
- Is this what you're looking for?
- Oh. Thank you, sir.

154
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:31,135
- Okay.
- [crowd cheering]

155
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,220
Aries.

156
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:33,971
Yes. I'm an Aries.

157
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,556
[crowd cheering]

158
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:37,683
Why would he say he's an Aries?

159
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:39,894
[music continues]

160
00:08:39,977 --> 00:08:41,646
Quee-- Queenie.

161
00:08:41,729 --> 00:08:44,232
Queenie is Aries. I know that well.
We share the same birthday.

162
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:45,733
[music continues]

163
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:57,578
Enzo is holding Queenie.

164
00:08:58,621 --> 00:08:59,997
He's the kidnapper.

165
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,374
[intense music playing]

166
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:04,585
That means, maybe he kidnapped Tonet too?

167
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:07,129
[rock music playing]

168
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,506
Where does Enzo live?

169
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:11,133
I don't know. We're not close.

170
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:14,011
You don't know, or you're an accomplice?

171
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,846
He has my sister!

172
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,099
That's enough!

173
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:20,893
We'll find him.

174
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:22,979
Let's go!

175
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:24,105
[music fades]

176
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:25,022
‪[door hinge squeaks]

177
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:39,912
[ominous music playing]

178
00:09:54,051 --> 00:09:55,052
[in English] I'm back.

179
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:05,730
[music continues]

180
00:10:08,899 --> 00:10:11,319
[gasps]

181
00:10:12,069 --> 00:10:13,529
[in English] Missed me, huh?

182
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:14,947
[gasps]

183
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,908
Mmm, that's your dinner.

184
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:19,577
[unsettling music playing]

185
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:21,370
Isn't that your favorite? Eat it.

186
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:23,539
I put effort into that.

187
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,124
[whimpers]

188
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:28,878
See? I'm still nice to you.

189
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:33,299
I should be starving you, so you'll learn.

190
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:35,217
[music continues]

191
00:10:37,219 --> 00:10:41,724
You're not nice. Liar, loser, demon!

192
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:44,477
- [shrieks]
- [Enzo] What?!

193
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:49,607
What?!

194
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,108
- [wails]
- What did you say?

195
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,109
[sobbing]

196
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:53,944
You don't want me anymore?

197
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:55,321
[scoffs]

198
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:57,657
That's fine, because
I don't want you either.

199
00:10:58,282 --> 00:10:59,909
Your replacement is already here.

200
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:03,954
She's in the living room, resting.

201
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:06,082
Do you know who?

202
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:07,249
[music swells]

203
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,334
Tonet.

204
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:12,838
- Tonet! Help me! [muffled]
- [grunts]

205
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:14,465
Enough! Shut up!

206
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:19,178
Keep quiet! Keep quiet!

207
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:22,932
- [sobbing]
- Shh!

208
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:29,021
- [sobs]
- [indistinct]

209
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,822
[wailing]

210
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:46,247
[wailing]

211
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:50,543
[music concludes]

212
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:57,216
Enzo's car isn't here anymore.
He usually parks here.

213
00:11:58,426 --> 00:11:59,885
You don't know the plate number?

214
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,220
‪[sinister music playing]

215
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:02,430
I told you, we're not close.

216
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:04,682
And I don't bother
memorizing plate numbers.

217
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:05,891
[music continues]

218
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:11,021
You know, you're a big showoff,
but you're useless.

219
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:13,399
You're Tonet's brother, right?

220
00:12:13,482 --> 00:12:15,943
Then why didn't you stop her
from going with people like Enzo?

221
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:17,069
Where were you?

222
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:19,363
You don't know anything about our issues.

223
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:23,742
[suspenseful music playing]

224
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:30,332
[disgusted scoff]

225
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:32,418
[grunts]

226
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:34,670
These tire marks from Enzo's car.

227
00:12:35,671 --> 00:12:36,797
These are…

228
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:39,800
- [Emerson] What's that?
- Goat droppings.

229
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:44,430
Is there a farm or goat pen nearby?

230
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:46,140
Yes.

231
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:49,935
[music continues]

232
00:12:52,396 --> 00:12:53,856
[music fades]

233
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:56,233
[crickets chirping]

234
00:12:57,651 --> 00:13:00,029
[anxious music playing]

235
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:02,656
[Tonet grunts]

236
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:05,326
[Tonet grunts]

237
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:09,288
[music continues]

238
00:13:09,371 --> 00:13:11,290
[thuds softly]

239
00:13:11,373 --> 00:13:13,125
[music fades]

240
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:19,298
[Enzo clears throat]

241
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:24,220
Tonet. We're here now.

242
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:26,138
Where are we?

243
00:13:27,014 --> 00:13:28,015
[Enzo] At my place.

244
00:13:28,724 --> 00:13:30,851
You didn't give me your address,

245
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:32,645
so I brought you here.

246
00:13:34,897 --> 00:13:36,774
But I gave you my address earlier.

247
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:42,112
I said Delfin's tailoring shop.

248
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:44,490
Ah, you passed out earlier.

249
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:45,991
It's better if you just rest here
for the meantime.

250
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:48,702
Once you're okay, I'll take you home.

251
00:13:48,786 --> 00:13:50,371
[unsettling music playing]

252
00:13:50,454 --> 00:13:52,164
[groans]

253
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:53,874
[ominous music playing]

254
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:56,168
Why does my head still hurt?

255
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:59,713
I'll get you some water. Stay there.

256
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:04,802
[music intensifies]

257
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:08,097
[foreboding music playing]

258
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:34,582
[wailing]

259
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:39,670
What's that?

260
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:41,922
Uh, that's my cat.

261
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:43,424
It's really mischievous.

262
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:47,261
[tense music playing]

263
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:56,896
[engine humming]

264
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,819
If something bad happens to my sister,

265
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:05,821
I'll never forgive myself.

266
00:15:06,614 --> 00:15:09,950
[sighs] My God, my God, my God!

267
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:14,747
Relax. Emerson, just relax.

268
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:16,415
Nothing like that will happen.

269
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:19,627
Come on. You're here. That won't happen.

270
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:21,879
[somber music playing]

271
00:15:21,962 --> 00:15:23,464
I'm not as good as you.

272
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:31,055
Emerson, between the two of us…

273
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:35,100
I know you won't allow
anything to happen to her,

274
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:37,353
because she's your sister.

275
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:41,357
Above all, I know
you love Tonet very much.

276
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,734
[music continues]

277
00:15:50,866 --> 00:15:54,828
[tense music playing]

278
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:13,138
[wailing]

279
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:20,270
[music continues]

280
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:29,863
[thuds]

281
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:31,615
[ominous music playing]

282
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:35,536
Finish that first.

283
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,372
Maybe your head hurts
because you're dehydrated.

284
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:39,289
Go on.

285
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:41,458
[ominous music playing]

286
00:16:45,462 --> 00:16:49,174
Uh… Can I see your cat?

287
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:51,343
Um, I can't let it out.

288
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:53,846
It's sick, and it bites.

289
00:16:54,513 --> 00:16:57,141
Better if you finish your water.

290
00:16:57,224 --> 00:17:00,894
[music continues]

291
00:17:06,775 --> 00:17:08,360
I'll just check on my cat.

292
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:12,990
[music continues]

293
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,534
‪[music intensifies]

294
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:22,791
Come here.

295
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,252
[bawls, then wails]

296
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:26,628
You just want attention!

297
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:30,340
[music continues]

298
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:37,347
[music fades]

299
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:39,016
Your replacement is already here,

300
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:40,726
so don't make any noise!

301
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,645
- [thumps]
- [groans]

302
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:46,857
- [Queenie wailing]
- [tense music playing]

303
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:53,697
- [grunts]
- [slaps]

304
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,783
[music continues]

305
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:58,077
[tense music playing]

306
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:09,713
[sighs]

307
00:18:10,714 --> 00:18:13,175
[foreboding music playing]

308
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:14,093
‪[gasps]

309
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:19,598
[wailing]

310
00:18:19,681 --> 00:18:21,809
[tense music playing]

311
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:23,811
[panting]

312
00:18:31,151 --> 00:18:35,405
- [gasping]
- [music continues]

313
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:52,256
[loud gasping]

314
00:18:54,424 --> 00:18:55,467
[Enzo] Tonet!

315
00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:58,679
Tonet, where are you?!

316
00:18:58,762 --> 00:19:02,057
[unsettling music playing]

317
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:03,142
Tonet!

318
00:19:03,851 --> 00:19:06,145
[music continues]

319
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:07,980
[Enzo] Tonet, where are you?!

320
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:11,066
[music continues]

321
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:21,577
Tonet!

322
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:24,621
[gasping]

323
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:34,548
[frantic music playing]

324
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:35,841
[screams]

325
00:19:35,924 --> 00:19:39,845
[music continues]

326
00:19:39,928 --> 00:19:40,929
Where do you think you're going, huh?

327
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:45,475
- [grunts and groans]
- [sobs]

328
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:47,060
What do you think, huh?

329
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:49,646
That I won't find you?

330
00:19:50,564 --> 00:19:52,608
No one escapes from me!

331
00:19:52,691 --> 00:19:55,277
[in English] You're mine now. Hmm, hmm?!

332
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,945
- Come here!
- [gasping]

333
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:59,072
You're running away, huh? What, hmm?

334
00:19:59,156 --> 00:20:00,866
You think you can escape? Hmm?

335
00:20:00,949 --> 00:20:02,075
I'm gonna get you!

336
00:20:02,159 --> 00:20:03,952
[Queenie wailing and grunting]

337
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:07,706
[grunting & panting]

338
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:12,377
[wailing, panting]

339
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:31,021
[Enzo] That's it. Just like that.

340
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:32,522
‪[panting]

341
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:35,901
[unsettling music playing]

342
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:37,402
[Enzo] Now you've got company.

343
00:20:38,403 --> 00:20:39,905
[suspicious music playing]

344
00:20:41,782 --> 00:20:43,909
[in English] Queenie, meet Tonet.

345
00:20:43,992 --> 00:20:45,577
[in English] Tonet, this is Queenie.

346
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:48,705
Why are you doing this to us?
[heavy breathing]

347
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:50,749
What did we ever do to you?!

348
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:53,585
- [Enzo sighs]
- [Tonet breathing heavily]

349
00:20:54,795 --> 00:20:57,089
You didn't do anything to me.

350
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:59,174
[in English] It's just that…

351
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,468
The three of us get along.

352
00:21:01,551 --> 00:21:05,013
And I want to be with you for a long time.

353
00:21:06,098 --> 00:21:08,725
But not like this, Enzo!

354
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:11,520
Let us go!

355
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:14,856
Shut up, shut up! Hands!

356
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:18,318
- [tense music playing]
- [Queenie muttering]

357
00:21:19,152 --> 00:21:20,654
Stop moving!

358
00:21:20,737 --> 00:21:21,571
‪[heavy breathing]

359
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:24,199
‪[Enzo groans]

360
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:28,161
[wailing]

361
00:21:28,245 --> 00:21:29,496
So, you'll both be the same.

362
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:31,081
[mutters and sobs]

363
00:21:31,164 --> 00:21:33,917
- Ah! Ahh!
- Mmm, ah!

364
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:36,336
[both wailing]

365
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:44,928
[music fades]

366
00:21:45,012 --> 00:21:47,973
[car engine humming]

367
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:58,859
[car engine stops]

368
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:02,738
- Oop, oop, oop, oop.
- Oh?

369
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:04,072
Where are you going?

370
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:06,116
No, I just have to go somewhere.

371
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:09,119
Where? Of course, to save my sister.

372
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:12,372
Emerson, don't be reckless.

373
00:22:12,456 --> 00:22:15,083
Enzo, you don't know
what he might do to you.

374
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:17,586
Okay, okay, okay. What… What's the plan?

375
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:18,503
What's the plan?

376
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:19,546
Nothing.

377
00:22:19,629 --> 00:22:21,465
- You stay here. That's the plan.
- [ominous music playing]

378
00:22:25,552 --> 00:22:27,179
[hushes]

379
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:30,223
[whispers] We've got company.

380
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:32,851
Girls, quiet. Don't make any noise.

381
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:36,021
- Huh?
- [mutters]

382
00:22:36,104 --> 00:22:39,191
[tense music playing]

383
00:22:40,609 --> 00:22:44,071
Hmm? Atoy, really?
What kind of plan is this?

384
00:22:44,571 --> 00:22:45,739
What if someone comes out
and sees me here?

385
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:47,324
What do I do then?

386
00:22:47,407 --> 00:22:48,784
[in English] Improvise.

387
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:51,036
Just don't reveal yourself,
don't get caught.

388
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:53,830
And above all, don't die.

389
00:22:53,914 --> 00:22:56,416
I don't need more problems.

390
00:22:57,167 --> 00:23:02,297
Fine. Just… make sure
you save Netchai, okay?

391
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:03,298
Don't mess this up.

392
00:23:03,381 --> 00:23:04,591
You too.

393
00:23:04,674 --> 00:23:06,301
[tense music playing]

394
00:23:06,384 --> 00:23:08,470
If you don't get out of there,
I will get in.

395
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:10,180
Just stay here.

396
00:23:10,263 --> 00:23:11,765
[music swells]

397
00:23:12,516 --> 00:23:16,019
[suspicious music playing]

398
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:21,191
[music continues]

399
00:23:23,944 --> 00:23:26,446
[inhales, then clicks tongue]

400
00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:29,658
[tense music playing]

401
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:34,538
Atoy…

402
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:39,126
[sobbing]

403
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:51,930
[sobbing continues]

404
00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:52,931
Come here.

405
00:23:54,057 --> 00:23:55,433
Queenie? You're Queenie?

406
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:56,977
You're Father Peping's niece?

407
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:58,270
[quivering breath]

408
00:23:58,353 --> 00:24:00,939
Your family's been looking for you.
[quivering breath]

409
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:02,566
How did you end up here?

410
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:05,944
Enzo and I just recently became friends.

411
00:24:06,611 --> 00:24:10,031
We both don't have parents,
so we got along.

412
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:11,992
[quivering breath]

413
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:14,911
One day we met, then my head hurt.

414
00:24:14,995 --> 00:24:17,497
When I woke up, I was here, Tonet.

415
00:24:17,581 --> 00:24:19,791
I was already here. [sobs]

416
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:22,711
Does he do this to all his female friends?

417
00:24:23,336 --> 00:24:24,838
[sobbing]

418
00:24:24,921 --> 00:24:25,922
There was--

419
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:28,175
There was another girl
locked up here before me.

420
00:24:28,258 --> 00:24:29,718
M-- Mandy.

421
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:31,428
Mandy. That was her name.

422
00:24:31,511 --> 00:24:33,805
He said I was Mandy's replacement.

423
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:37,392
He brought her out,
and I never saw her again.

424
00:24:37,475 --> 00:24:39,603
I never saw Mandy again.

425
00:24:39,686 --> 00:24:42,022
She's been missing for a month.

426
00:24:42,105 --> 00:24:43,565
- [quivering breath]
- [inaudible]

427
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:44,858
A month?

428
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:48,320
[quivering breath]

429
00:24:48,403 --> 00:24:52,115
Tonet. Tonet, you're the one
he's replacing me with.

430
00:24:52,199 --> 00:24:54,826
Don't-- Don't let him take me, Tonet.
Tonet, please.

431
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:56,077
Don't let him take me, Tonet.

432
00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:57,913
Tonet, please.

433
00:24:57,996 --> 00:25:00,123
[sobbing]

434
00:25:00,207 --> 00:25:03,043
Tonet, don't let him take me, please.

435
00:25:03,126 --> 00:25:04,085
[hushes]

436
00:25:04,169 --> 00:25:05,086
[Enzo] Wow!

437
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:06,421
[Queenie] Tonet… [gasps]

438
00:25:06,504 --> 00:25:08,340
[Enzo] So, you're best friends now, huh?

439
00:25:08,423 --> 00:25:09,758
[both gasping]

440
00:25:09,841 --> 00:25:10,967
Stand up, both of you.

441
00:25:11,051 --> 00:25:13,845
Stand up. Let her go.

442
00:25:13,929 --> 00:25:15,889
- Let go, let go!
- [Queenie] No, no!

443
00:25:15,972 --> 00:25:17,682
[Enzo] Stand up! Stand up!

444
00:25:17,766 --> 00:25:21,269
- [groans]
- [tense music playing]

445
00:25:21,353 --> 00:25:24,022
You too, stand up.

446
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:26,441
- [music intensifies]
- [Queenie] No.

447
00:25:27,484 --> 00:25:31,571
[music continues]

448
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:36,743
[crickets chirping]

449
00:25:52,259 --> 00:25:54,219
[ominous music playing]

450
00:26:03,603 --> 00:26:04,729
Who are you?

451
00:26:05,355 --> 00:26:06,481
What are you doing here?

452
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:11,027
- [intense music playing]
- [electronic blipping]

453
00:26:19,327 --> 00:26:21,162
[Atoy] Son of a thread.

454
00:26:21,246 --> 00:26:22,872
[Emerson] What she needs is a brother,

455
00:26:22,956 --> 00:26:24,499
not a kidnapper.

456
00:26:24,582 --> 00:26:26,418
[grunting and groaning]

457
00:26:26,501 --> 00:26:27,669
[Emerson] Netchai!

458
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:28,878
[grunts]

459
00:26:28,962 --> 00:26:30,839
[thuds, then clatters]

460
00:26:30,922 --> 00:26:31,840
[clatters, then thuds]

461
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:33,300
I'll take care of you. Keep quiet.

462
00:26:33,383 --> 00:26:34,426
[grunting and groaning]

463
00:26:34,509 --> 00:26:36,261
[thumping and thudding]

464
00:26:36,344 --> 00:26:37,929
Atoy! Don't…

465
00:26:38,013 --> 00:26:39,681
[grunts and thumps]

466
00:26:39,764 --> 00:26:41,141
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

467
00:26:41,224 --> 00:26:43,351
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

468
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:44,853
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪
